  "prompt": "Can an iPhone be used as a reliable guitar tuner?",
  "response": "Yes, iPhones can be used as reliable guitar tuners through various methods:\n\n1. Built-in Tuner Apps\n- Many free and paid tuner apps are available in the App Store\n- Examples include GuitarTuna, Boss Tuner, and Pro Guitar Tuner\n- Most offer accurate chromatic tuning for multiple instruments\n\n2. Accuracy\n- Modern tuner apps use the iPhone's microphone to detect pitch\n- Most are quite accurate, especially in quiet environments\n- Some apps offer visual and audio feedback\n\n3. Special Features\n- Some apps provide multiple tuning modes (standard, drop tunings)\n- Advanced apps can help with alternate and custom tunings\n- Many include metronome and chord reference features\n\n4. Hardware Add-ons\n- Clip-on tuners that connect to iPhone for enhanced accuracy\n- External microphones can improve sound detection\n\n5. Limitations\n- Background noise can affect accuracy\n- Best used in relatively quiet settings\n- Some professional musicians prefer dedicated hardware tuners\n\nOverall, an iPhone can be a reliable and convenient guitar tuning tool for most musicians, especially with good-quality tuner apps.",
